      "content": "thanks, that makes sense. i can definitely see how that's the standard in places like london or nyc. \n\nbut i want to make sure this guide is actually \"universal.\" if i'm writing for a global audience, how should i handle it when someone's natural grooming or style doesn't fit that \"neutral\" or \"tailored\" look? like, if they have distinct cultural hairstyles or wear traditional clothing that's more colorful/complex than a suit—how do i frame that in the guide without making them seem less \"professional\" than the western baseline?",
